This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with personalized recommendation algorithms. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm to balance accuracy and fairness. Additionally, it may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it considers the impact of fairness on multiple stakeholders in a recommender system. It could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CY) sub-category as fairness is a key concern in security and privacy. Finally, it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category as it proposes a new algorithm to ensure fairness in a recommender system.
